<doc id="907428" wikidata="Q15999446" url="?curid=907428" title="James Stanley Freeman">
<text>James Stanley Freeman (May 12, 1874 in Jasper, Alabama – April 26, 1960 in Jasper, AL), known as &quot;Big Jim&quot;, was an Alabama millionaire in the early 20th century. 

He was famous for making and losing over a million dollars twice before 1900. Freeman retired as one of the wealthiest men in the Southern United States. He and his wife, Willie Lee Shepherd, had one son, James Shepherd Freeman, a World War II admiral. His grandson was James Shepherd Freeman Jr.</text><links>
